<br />
1)Lacluster sets:<br />
I disagree with you. Ok, lot of set haven&#39;t the power cards of the fellowship set, but their interest lie in other places. Lot of common and uncommon cards had changed the way the game is played. You are focusing on self-evident main cards. Try the subtle way: Gollum, fell beast, lot of Rotk set help you avoid hand clog. I remember the firsts articles about Lotr speaking of card efficiency and card drawing... This is card efficiency, now you can see all your deck and choose what card your are going to keep and what card your are going to trash. The sets are, in my opinion, more geared for veterans than for novices players.<br />
The time of the "must have in the deck cards" is fading away (for the greater good of the game). I remeber the time of SWCCG and the escalation of "power cards", it was a bad time and a race to arms difficult to afford by many players.<br />
Now for Lotr, we have a game that evolve around concept and not around cards. Don&#39;t try to find a card more powerful than Aragorn&#39;s bow, greenleaf or Path, try to think different.<br />
<br />
2)horrible marketing.<br />
Ok, decipher isn&#39;t really organised in this department but anthologies and countdown had attracted lots of new players by giving them the real power cards at low price: you want eomer, aragorn&#39;s bow, greenleaf (and the other)? You just have to spend about 250 in 5 month and you get them all.<br />
How many boxes do you need to achieve that? About 8? Or maybe 12? Taking the low figure 8*100=800, for a profit for newbies of about 550 (+/- 700$). <br />
And for veteran? Players in my area had liked these promotion for two reason: a) some had completed their stock of power card (fourth path, servant and other difficult to find cards), b) they have cards to exchange to newbies.<br />
<br />
3)Tournament<br />
I agree with most of your comments on this point. Tournaments are the backbone of every game and the new system is hurting attendency.<br />
<br />
4)Mismanagement.<br />
<br />
Don&#39;t know about this.<br />
<br />
5)Conclusion.<br />
"Les torts sont partages". Decipher make some bad decision about the infrastructure of the game, but the cards themselves with some imaginations aren&#39;t that bad.<br />
I think that outre-atlantique, you really need to learn the difference between having big guns and using them.  <font size=1>(+4 tp, Double-Edged Sword)</font><BR>
